sentences: David Le Chaine Hollister (born August 17, 1968) is an American R&B singer who found fame during the 1990s as one quarter of the R&B quartet Blackstreet, before going on to have a solo career.
Hollister is best known for his 2000 gold-certified album Chicago '85...
The Movie, which included the singles "One Woman Man" and "Take Care of Home".
He was also featured on Tupac Shakur's hit singles "Brenda's Got a Baby" and "Keep Ya Head Up".
